analysis.info:
aBSREL (Adaptive branch-site random effects likelihood)
                            uses an adaptive random effects branch-site model framework
                            to test whether each branch has evolved under positive selection,
                            using a procedure which infers an optimal number of rate categories per branch.
analysis.citation: Less Is More: An Adaptive Branch-Site Random Effects Model for Efficient Detection of Episodic Diversifying Selection (2015). Mol Biol Evol 32 (5): 1342-1353
analysis.authors: Sergei L Kosakovsky Pond, Ben Murrell, Steven Weaver and Temple iGEM / UCSD viral evolution group
analysis.requirements: in-frame codon alignment and a phylogenetic tree
